# Lesson 2 - Creating My First Enterprise Server

## Objective

Create my first Windows Server 2022 virtual machine.

## Server Name

TS-DC01

## Purpose

This virtual machine will become the Domain Controller for my simulated enterprise environment, TechSolutions Pty Ltd.

## What I Learned

A Domain Controller is responsible for authenticating users, managing permissions, and enforcing security policies across an organisation.

## Next Step

Configure the virtual hardware and install Windows Server 2022.

## Lesson 2 – Hardware Allocation

### Configuration

**Virtual Machine:** TS-DC01

**Memory:** 4096 MB

**Processors:** 2 vCPUs

### Why I Chose These Settings

The configuration provides enough resources for Windows Server 2022 while maintaining good performance on the host laptop. It also allows room for future services such as Active Directory, DNS and DHCP.

### Lesson Learned

Resource allocation is a balance. Assigning too little memory can reduce server performance, while assigning too much can negatively affect the host system.

## Virtual Disk Configuration

### Disk Size

60 GB

### Allocation Method

Dynamically Allocated

### Why I Chose This

The disk is large enough to support Windows Server 2022 and future services such as Active Directory, DNS and DHCP while conserving physical disk space on the host laptop.

### Lesson Learned

Virtual machines use virtual disk files (VDI) that behave like physical hard drives to the guest operating system.

